    {
      "id": "1a2f8d8d_f2526212",
      "file_path": "controlloop/templates/archetype-cl-amsterdam/src/main/resources/archetype-resources/src/main/resources/__closedLoopControlName__.drl",
      "patchset_number": 5,
      "line": 590,
      "message": "I asked Daniel about the else case to make sure wouldn't break other use cases and have some concerns about hitting null pointer exceptions in the finishOperation.   \n\nCan you talk to Daniel to see if we can have an alternative solution, or we can leave like this, and tackle a more permanent solution in another review?\n\nWhat do you think?",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 477,
        "name": "Jorge Hernandez",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jorge.hernandez-herrero@att.com",
        "username": "jhh"
      },
      "updated": "2017-10-17 18:51:54.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "1a2f8d8d_52b9362d",
      "file_path": "controlloop/templates/archetype-cl-amsterdam/src/main/resources/archetype-resources/src/main/resources/__closedLoopControlName__.drl",
      "patchset_number": 5,
      "line": 590,
      "message": "When I tested this for vDNS it is the operationRequest that is null as a result of a failed named query. So what I can do is set the policyResult to \"FAILURE\" so that there are no null values when it gets to finishOperation. The result of finishOperation will then be: Finishing VF Module Create result is Failure. I think it's okay to keep this solution for vDNS only",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 1757,
        "name": "Ali Hockla",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "ah999m@att.com",
        "username": "ah999m"
      },
      "updated": "2017-10-17 19:50:23.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "1a2f8d8d_f2526212",
      "unresolved": false
